1
00:00:19,040 --> 00:00:23,719
That's me, Jaak.
I am 8 years old in this photo

2
00:00:23,720 --> 00:00:28,219
I live in Tallinn, in a newly-built
residential area called Oismae...

3
00:00:28,220 --> 00:00:32,836
that is always expanding

4
00:00:34,320 --> 00:00:40,348
My life is wonderful,
because I can watch Finnish TV

5
00:00:42,520 --> 00:00:46,279
My father taught me
how to take photographs

6
00:00:46,280 --> 00:00:50,078
Now I take photos of everything
that matters to me

7
00:00:52,440 --> 00:00:54,839
The first photos I take are of...

8
00:00:54,840 --> 00:01:00,316
commercials and films
shown on Finnish TV

9
00:01:01,900 --> 00:01:04,799
Here, our relatives from
Southern Estonia are visiting us

10
00:01:04,800 --> 00:01:06,379
They can't see Finnish TV there

11
00:01:06,380 --> 00:01:12,068
It's Friday evening.
We're watching "Dallas", as always

12
00:01:12,780 --> 00:01:17,209
But our relatives see "Dallas"
for the very first time

13
00:01:18,280 --> 00:01:21,459
And they see a completely different "Dallas"

14
00:01:21,460 --> 00:01:23,879
It is a captivating, spiritual seance...

15
00:01:23,880 --> 00:01:26,379
and my mother is the medium

16
00:01:26,380 --> 00:01:30,039
She interprets everything about
the strange characters...

17
00:01:30,040 --> 00:01:34,552
their love affairs and relationships

18
00:01:36,160 --> 00:01:41,359
But for the first time in their lives,
our relatives see...

19
00:01:41,360 --> 00:01:46,839
people drinking whisky on the
rocks and working in skyscrapers

20
00:01:46,940 --> 00:01:51,779
Men with perfect teeth and
beautiful, yet unhappy, women

21
00:01:51,780 --> 00:01:55,555
And they are all millionaires

22
00:01:56,680 --> 00:02:01,719
Then I promised Urve, my niece,
to write her every week...

23
00:02:01,720 --> 00:02:06,939
about what is happening in "Dallas",
so she wouldn't lose her connection...

24
00:02:06,940 --> 00:02:11,937
to that "real world"
she met at our home in Tallinn

25
00:02:28,820 --> 00:02:32,839
In the beginning, there was
Miss Ellie and old Jock...

26
00:02:32,840 --> 00:02:38,119
Bobby came too...
The police was there...

27
00:02:38,120 --> 00:02:42,351
Everyone suspected Sue Ellen...

28
00:02:51,510 --> 00:02:55,279
A film by Jaak Kilmi and Kiur Aarma

29
00:02:57,380 --> 00:03:03,355
DISCO AND ATOMIC WAR

30
00:03:07,280 --> 00:03:14,399
POEM: "The holidays aren't for slumbering,
get up and spread the joy"

31
00:03:14,400 --> 00:03:21,079
"I wake up early and wash up,
I wash my little brother too"

32
00:03:21,080 --> 00:03:24,399
"We run to the window,
a parade is passing"

33
00:03:24,400 --> 00:03:28,999
"Oh, why are there so few
of these great holidays?"

34
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:31,939
We grew up during the Cold War

35
00:03:31,940 --> 00:03:36,119
Estonia was occupied
and a part of the Soviet Union

36
00:03:36,120 --> 00:03:42,529
Long live May 1st!
The International Day of Solidarity!

37
00:03:44,460 --> 00:03:47,716
Long live the Soviet Union!

38
00:03:51,200 --> 00:03:56,793
There was an iron curtain
between us and the free world

39
00:03:57,120 --> 00:04:00,395
But radio waves seeped through it

40
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:04,719
And they sounded as if they weren't
coming from across the ocean...

41
00:04:04,720 --> 00:04:07,676
but from the bottom of it

42
00:04:13,480 --> 00:04:18,559
1,400 jamming stations in the USSR
transmitted static and whistling...

43
00:04:18,560 --> 00:04:21,519
in between the wavelengths
of Western stations

44
00:04:21,520 --> 00:04:26,274
Back then, radio was Estonia's
only connection to the free world

45
00:04:42,520 --> 00:04:47,739
In the 1950s, the world
enters an era of television

46
00:04:47,740 --> 00:04:51,870
In Tallinn, Soviet Estonian TV
(ETV) begins its broadcasts

47
00:04:53,800 --> 00:04:59,352
Good evening, comrades.
Estonian Television begins its broadcasting

48
00:05:00,760 --> 00:05:07,756
From us, in Tallinn, TV waves are
also spreading 80 km northward...

49
00:05:07,760 --> 00:05:12,830
where Helsinki, the capital
of Finland, happens to be

50
00:05:13,400 --> 00:05:19,449
But the Finns don't have their own
national TV channel yet

51
00:05:21,960 --> 00:05:27,954
The same year, Soviet Estonian TV launches
its Finnish-language programming...

52
00:05:27,960 --> 00:05:30,999
where you can see happy
Soviet workers talking

53
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:34,039
...then, the workers
are happy about it

54
00:05:34,040 --> 00:05:38,439
The workers are happy
about automating the process

55
00:05:38,440 --> 00:05:44,439
Today, more and more production
is expected from everyone...

56
00:05:44,440 --> 00:05:48,034
...so automating the process
is natural

57
00:05:48,660 --> 00:05:53,159
It's clear that this
propaganda channel was...

58
00:05:53,160 --> 00:05:59,599
directed at Finland to spread
their red ideology here

59
00:05:59,600 --> 00:06:03,979
We're amidst the Cold War and
Finland is no-man's-land

60
00:06:03,980 --> 00:06:06,219
An outwardly Western country where...

61
00:06:06,220 --> 00:06:10,659
nothing happens without
permission from Moscow

62
00:06:11,200 --> 00:06:15,079
There are Soviet military bases
in Finland

63
00:06:15,080 --> 00:06:19,759
The are rumours that the Russians
are setting up TV transmitters...

64
00:06:19,760 --> 00:06:24,659
in their bases to drown Finland
in Communist propaganda

65
00:06:24,660 --> 00:06:28,039
The Western secret services
are afraid of...

66
00:06:28,040 --> 00:06:31,734
completely losing Finland
to the Russians

67
00:06:32,920 --> 00:06:39,999
The fight took place mostly
in countries like Finland

68
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:43,599
The fight for souls

69
00:06:43,600 --> 00:06:46,279
American diplomats in Finland realise...

70
00:06:46,280 --> 00:06:48,839
that it is time to fight back

71
00:06:48,840 --> 00:06:52,439
The secret telegrams from
the U.S. embassy to Washington...

72
00:06:52,440 --> 00:06:54,919
demand an immediate response...

73
00:06:54,920 --> 00:06:59,037
for launching Finnish TV
with Western support

74
00:07:03,160 --> 00:07:07,119
And so it goes. Two years
after Soviet Estonia...

75
00:07:07,120 --> 00:07:10,359
the Finns launch their own TV channel

76
00:07:10,360 --> 00:07:13,799
At first, it is predictably
mild and cautious...

77
00:07:13,800 --> 00:07:18,153
Welcome to our Christmas programme...

78
00:07:23,680 --> 00:07:26,079
Then occurred the Prague Spring...

79
00:07:26,080 --> 00:07:29,399
Czechoslovakia's uprising
against the Communist regime

80
00:07:29,400 --> 00:07:32,039
Soviet Estonian media doesn't
cover the uprising...

81
00:07:32,040 --> 00:07:34,599
as if nothing had happened

82
00:07:34,600 --> 00:07:39,519
Soviet TV shows the
following images:

83
00:07:39,520 --> 00:07:44,359
Here, the Czech people
welcome their Soviet guests

84
00:07:44,360 --> 00:07:50,194
Here, you can see a lady chanting:
"Friendship! Friendship!"

85
00:07:52,960 --> 00:07:59,039
80 km north of us, the Finns
see the following report:

86
00:07:59,040 --> 00:08:02,479
Czechoslovakia has been
occupied for five days now

87
00:08:02,480 --> 00:08:05,799
Large foreign troops are on the
move, especially in Slovakia

88
00:08:05,800 --> 00:08:08,756
New units are brought in

89
00:08:09,360 --> 00:08:12,359
This morning, the official
government of Czechoslovakia...

90
00:08:12,360 --> 00:08:16,359
denied the Soviet news agency
TASS announcement...

91
00:08:16,360 --> 00:08:19,679
which claimed there are armed
cars moving through Prague

92
00:08:19,680 --> 00:08:28,010
Quite the opposite, the Soviet occupiers
are shooting ordinary people for no reason

93
00:08:34,700 --> 00:08:44,553
The next day, an anti-Soviet demonstration
rages in Helsinki, the first since the war

94
00:08:44,640 --> 00:08:50,559
It was very upsetting.
And a big disappointment...

95
00:08:50,560 --> 00:08:57,192
for those who believed in the possibility
of a humane socialism

96
00:08:58,620 --> 00:09:01,159
Here, the policemen
in white gloves...

97
00:09:01,160 --> 00:09:05,039
remove some of the loudest
students from the Soviet embassy

98
00:09:05,040 --> 00:09:07,559
But the Russians are still very upset

99
00:09:07,560 --> 00:09:10,419
At the same time,
the Finnish TV director's car...

100
00:09:10,420 --> 00:09:15,312
enters the embassy
through the back gate

101
00:09:15,700 --> 00:09:20,119
The TV station is held responsible.
The director is ordered to explain...

102
00:09:20,120 --> 00:09:23,679
why Finnish TV is spreading
lies and hysteria...

103
00:09:23,680 --> 00:09:26,729
and ruining their friendly relationship
with the Soviet Union

104
00:09:26,730 --> 00:09:31,799
It upset them very much.
But they couldn't do anything

105
00:09:31,800 --> 00:09:36,939
The show had already aired.
And we didn't regret it either

106
00:09:38,560 --> 00:09:44,799
In Tallinn, we watch the Finnish coverage
of Prague with interest and concern

107
00:09:44,800 --> 00:09:50,237
By then, there are TV sets in most
Soviet Estonian homes

108
00:09:51,060 --> 00:09:58,673
Then a new transmitter starts
construction near Helsinki

109
00:10:05,200 --> 00:10:07,559
However, the specialists
notice at once...

110
00:10:07,560 --> 00:10:10,479
that there's something very
strange going on

111
00:10:10,480 --> 00:10:14,799
The Espoo transmitter wasn't directed
only at the Finnish mainland...

112
00:10:14,800 --> 00:10:17,239
it had a circular diagram

113
00:10:17,240 --> 00:10:25,229
At least half of the transmitter's
coverage was directed southward...

114
00:10:25,230 --> 00:10:28,130
towards the Gulf of Finland

115
00:10:32,320 --> 00:10:37,450
Are the practical-minded Finns
heating the Gulf just for fun?

116
00:10:37,480 --> 00:10:42,598
Edward Lucas has done extensive
research on the Cold War

117
00:10:57,220 --> 00:11:04,279
Western countries probably knew
that Finnish TV broadcasts...

118
00:11:04,280 --> 00:11:09,309
reached Tallinn and
Northern Estonia as well

119
00:11:09,520 --> 00:11:13,639
Naturally, the Soviet media thinks
Americans are behind this

120
00:11:13,640 --> 00:11:16,519
They report that the mast was built
by an American company

121
00:11:16,520 --> 00:11:19,599
Even more, they have built it
high enough...

122
00:11:19,600 --> 00:11:23,219
for ideological waves
to reach Estonia

123
00:11:23,220 --> 00:11:24,939
A newspaper rages:

124
00:11:24,940 --> 00:11:28,519
"The Capitalist government of
Finland and the U.S. propagandists..."

125
00:11:28,520 --> 00:11:34,199
"mean to dehumanise the Soviet people,
especially the youth..."

126
00:11:34,200 --> 00:11:38,372
"with violence, cruelty
and sexual looseness"

127
00:11:38,373 --> 00:11:49,158
They wrote that Finland wanted to
dehumanise the Estonian youth

128
00:11:49,159 --> 00:11:55,399
That we were transmitting shows
to Estonia on purpose

129
00:11:55,400 --> 00:11:58,914
It was complete nonsense!

130
00:12:02,040 --> 00:12:06,599
Naturally, a forest of antennas
emerges on the rooftops of Tallinn...

131
00:12:06,600 --> 00:12:10,079
its branches stretching
towards Finland

132
00:12:10,080 --> 00:12:13,559
But you can't watch Finnish TV
with a Soviet TV set

133
00:12:13,560 --> 00:12:16,519
The technical standard is different

134
00:12:16,520 --> 00:12:19,559
You could see the black and white
images on Finnish TV...

135
00:12:19,560 --> 00:12:22,851
but there was no sound

136
00:12:30,080 --> 00:12:35,639
This is me, Joosep. And the weight
of our family's big secret...

137
00:12:35,640 --> 00:12:39,119
is reflected in my eyes

138
00:12:39,120 --> 00:12:44,139
When I was 9, our entire family
was involved in illegal business

139
00:12:44,140 --> 00:12:47,579
Me, my father and mother

140
00:12:47,580 --> 00:12:52,919
I knew that you could end up
in prison for things like that

141
00:12:52,920 --> 00:12:58,230
So we had a strict procedure
concerning the telephone

142
00:13:00,900 --> 00:13:05,095
It had to ring eight times

143
00:13:05,096 --> 00:13:10,679
Then the caller hung up
and redialled immediately

144
00:13:10,680 --> 00:13:13,159
Only then could we pick up
the phone

145
00:13:13,160 --> 00:13:16,259
That was how my father's
clients called him

146
00:13:16,260 --> 00:13:20,019
My father was an electronics engineer
at Tallinn Polytechnic

147
00:13:20,020 --> 00:13:23,719
But he earned much more for
building Finnish TV converters

148
00:13:23,720 --> 00:13:30,214
He built them at home, in his room
with heavy brown curtains drawn

149
00:13:30,215 --> 00:13:35,793
I think all of father's colleagues
were building these blocks

150
00:13:39,260 --> 00:13:45,159
The ideological virus spreading fast
from the West worries Moscow

151
00:13:45,160 --> 00:13:49,613
The evil hand of the CIA
is seen behind every move

152
00:13:50,214 --> 00:13:52,814
"TUPLA chocolate bar -
enough for two"

153
00:13:55,020 --> 00:13:57,839
Soviet propaganda
fires back fiercely

154
00:13:57,840 --> 00:14:00,439
In the State House of Political Education...

155
00:14:00,440 --> 00:14:03,719
a room for the methods of
counterpropaganda is established

156
00:14:03,720 --> 00:14:07,119
There, every propagandist can
quickly get a clear and...

157
00:14:07,120 --> 00:14:11,696
in-depth overview of the methods
of counterpropaganda

158
00:14:15,300 --> 00:14:18,119
In the Soviet films of our childhood...

159
00:14:18,120 --> 00:14:24,619
the American secret services cruelly
hunt innocent Soviet people

160
00:14:33,860 --> 00:14:38,399
The KGB gets a new leader,
Yuri Andropov, who is...

161
00:14:38,400 --> 00:14:43,759
the man behind the bloody
suppression of the Prague Spring

162
00:14:43,760 --> 00:14:46,039
He is a tough leader...

163
00:14:46,040 --> 00:14:49,279
in control of the biggest
secret service in the world...

164
00:14:49,280 --> 00:14:54,472
with thousands of agents
in hundreds of countries

165
00:14:59,720 --> 00:15:02,479
Somewhere here,
in the KGB headquarters...

166
00:15:02,480 --> 00:15:07,559
there is a special task force
for fighting the Western influence

167
00:15:07,560 --> 00:15:13,779
They are responsible for what
goes on in our heads

168
00:15:20,480 --> 00:15:28,419
Moscow sends a high KGB officer to head
a special committee inspecting Estonia

169
00:15:28,420 --> 00:15:33,279
Secretly, a group of Estonian sociologists
are assigned to the committee

170
00:15:33,280 --> 00:15:36,159
They are led by Hagi Shein, who,
as fate would have it...

171
00:15:36,160 --> 00:15:39,259
later becomes the head of Estonian TV

172
00:15:39,260 --> 00:15:41,319
It was a secret study designed to...

173
00:15:41,320 --> 00:15:45,999
observe the Estonian viewers'
attitude towards Finnish TV

174
00:15:46,000 --> 00:15:49,850
Especially young people's attitude

175
00:15:55,080 --> 00:16:00,914
Finnish TV had become the most
watched channel in Estonia

176
00:16:00,960 --> 00:16:06,719
The results were definitely worrisome
for the ideologists in Moscow

177
00:16:06,720 --> 00:16:09,939
It bothered them,
it called for counteraction

178
00:16:09,940 --> 00:16:13,899
Moscow sends orders to drown out
the Finnish TV signal

179
00:16:13,900 --> 00:16:16,759
More and more TV masts
are built in Estonia...

180
00:16:16,760 --> 00:16:20,969
bombing the waves with
Soviet programming

181
00:16:23,640 --> 00:16:27,019
Our home coast, the southern
coast of the Gulf of Finland...

182
00:16:27,020 --> 00:16:29,939
one of the most beautiful
places in the world...

183
00:16:29,940 --> 00:16:34,000
has become the front line
of the Cold War!

184
00:16:36,200 --> 00:16:39,359
But the American response
is clever

185
00:16:39,360 --> 00:16:45,439
They are ready to bring out their new,
invisible weapon

186
00:16:46,140 --> 00:16:53,679
Behind it, there was a skilled,
even genius, tactical plan...

187
00:16:53,680 --> 00:16:57,159
for breaking up the Communist Bloc

188
00:16:57,560 --> 00:17:02,439
Georgi Potcheptsov is a renowned
expert on ideological warfare

189
00:17:02,440 --> 00:17:07,774
He has thoroughly researched
the methods of the Americans

190
00:17:08,320 --> 00:17:13,233
Americans did a lot of work
with deflectors and tourists

191
00:17:13,320 --> 00:17:16,231
You're a Soviet spy?
- No!

192
00:17:16,680 --> 00:17:23,859
They were trying to understand
the nature of the Soviet person

193
00:17:23,860 --> 00:17:30,430
Their minds were studied and
analysed to find a way inside

194
00:17:31,240 --> 00:17:34,631
And it was found!

195
00:17:41,080 --> 00:17:46,799
I have met people who have met
the head of CIA

196
00:17:46,800 --> 00:17:49,319
Their plans were very precise...

197
00:17:49,320 --> 00:17:54,439
regarding the means to use
in conquering the viewer

198
00:17:54,440 --> 00:17:59,999
The chosen battlefield was what is now
known as "soft power"'

199
00:18:00,000 --> 00:18:04,710
It was television, popular culture

200
00:18:22,760 --> 00:18:27,479
There's the hard, forceful
power, like a tank...

201
00:18:27,480 --> 00:18:31,711
and there's soft, entertaining
power, like a film

202
00:18:44,040 --> 00:18:46,559
Finnish TV shows "Ninotchka"...

203
00:18:46,560 --> 00:18:50,319
a feature film starring
the marvellous Greta Garbo

204
00:18:50,320 --> 00:18:52,679
It is a story about
a female Soviet commissary...

205
00:18:52,680 --> 00:18:54,959
who falls in love with
an American...

206
00:18:54,960 --> 00:18:58,596
and betrays
the Communist ideals

207
00:19:04,800 --> 00:19:08,439
For Moscow, showing that film
is a direct anti-Soviet act

208
00:19:08,440 --> 00:19:11,679
So much so that the heads
of Finnish TV...

209
00:19:11,680 --> 00:19:16,117
are called to Moscow
for a very serious talk

210
00:19:22,400 --> 00:19:25,879
The Soviet Estonian party leaders
have their own suggestion...

211
00:19:25,880 --> 00:19:28,039
a device should be developed...

212
00:19:28,040 --> 00:19:31,399
to create captions for
Finnish broadcasts...

213
00:19:31,400 --> 00:19:36,770
to overthrow the false
information! For example:

214
00:19:40,760 --> 00:19:44,959
Disinformation! Champagne has been
produced in the USSR since 1928

215
00:19:44,960 --> 00:19:48,979
That plan is found to be "at present,
impossible to carry out"

216
00:19:48,980 --> 00:19:51,999
Or, to put it more simply,
nonsense

217
00:19:52,000 --> 00:19:57,739
But the threat of the Russians
jamming the TV waves remains

218
00:19:57,740 --> 00:20:01,479
By that time, Finnish TV has become
one of the main cracks...

219
00:20:01,480 --> 00:20:07,371
for soft power to seep into
the Soviet Union unhindered

220
00:20:11,180 --> 00:20:14,639
In Estonia, the underground
production of Finnish TV guides...

221
00:20:14,640 --> 00:20:18,979
is a growing business
- At 7:40...

222
00:20:18,980 --> 00:20:21,879
My grandfather had a friend
from wartime, Endel...

223
00:20:21,880 --> 00:20:27,479
who worked in the district committee
(Endel) Did you get that?

224
00:20:27,480 --> 00:20:29,879
My grandfather was
a school headmaster...

225
00:20:29,880 --> 00:20:31,959
and he had a typing machine
in his office

226
00:20:31,960 --> 00:20:35,079
So Endel gave the TV guide
to my grandfather...

227
00:20:35,080 --> 00:20:38,479
and my mother got
a typed copy from him

228
00:20:38,480 --> 00:20:40,999
Mother worked in a hospital

229
00:20:41,000 --> 00:20:45,239
In the evenings, I helped her to
copy the Finnish TV guides

230
00:20:45,240 --> 00:20:48,559
My mother sold them at work
for one rouble a piece...

231
00:20:48,560 --> 00:20:53,575
I got 10 kopecks for each copy

232
00:20:55,780 --> 00:21:00,159
Because of these TV guides,
I was a made man at school

233
00:21:00,160 --> 00:21:04,879
At one point, we pulled a prank
with a couple of friends

234
00:21:04,880 --> 00:21:08,150
I typed into the TV guides...

235
00:21:08,151 --> 00:21:11,751
"Sex film at 2 AM"

236
00:21:11,800 --> 00:21:13,979
I don't know if it's true...

237
00:21:13,980 --> 00:21:19,468
but there were rumours of
many lit windows that night

238
00:21:22,660 --> 00:21:30,919
The fight for the souls of our
generation begins in 1975

239
00:21:30,920 --> 00:21:34,539
Although many of us
aren't born yet

240
00:21:34,540 --> 00:21:40,269
The western countries make
a clever deal with the Russians

241
00:21:43,460 --> 00:21:47,119
Today, the Soviet delegation
arrives in the Finnish capital...

242
00:21:47,120 --> 00:21:49,359
to participate in the final stage...

243
00:21:49,360 --> 00:21:52,199
of the Conference on Security
and Cooperation in Europe

244
00:21:52,200 --> 00:21:54,679
The delegation is led by
comrade Leonid Brezhnev...

245
00:21:54,680 --> 00:21:58,659
the Secretary General
of the Communist Party of USSR

246
00:21:58,660 --> 00:22:00,079
The other members
of the delegation are...

247
00:22:00,080 --> 00:22:06,179
Here, Brezhnev is signing
the Helsinki Agreement

248
00:22:06,180 --> 00:22:10,319
The areas of influence of the sides
of the Cold War are laid out

249
00:22:10,320 --> 00:22:12,219
The Western countries promise...

250
00:22:12,220 --> 00:22:14,579
not to meddle with the Soviet
sphere of influence

251
00:22:14,580 --> 00:22:17,819
In return, the USSR promises
not to jam the TV waves

252
00:22:17,820 --> 00:22:21,397
The hook has been swallowed!

253
00:22:21,720 --> 00:22:26,559
The Soviet Union probably thought
that the borders were now sealed

254
00:22:26,560 --> 00:22:31,759
But, instead, they started to crack -
with more freedom of speech...

255
00:22:31,760 --> 00:22:35,558
and other citizens' rights

256
00:22:45,520 --> 00:22:50,990
Disco has become very popular
among the young people

257
00:22:50,991 --> 00:22:55,991
But adults find this
dance move difficult

258
00:22:57,160 --> 00:23:02,039
And then, one night, they showed
these moves on Finnish TV

259
00:23:02,040 --> 00:23:06,959
One, two, three, four.
Let's lift our knees

260
00:23:06,960 --> 00:23:11,669
And now, let's... disco!

261
00:23:15,980 --> 00:23:20,514
Now, disco was everywhere,
including our school

262
00:23:25,180 --> 00:23:29,452
These songs were stuck
in our heads...

263
00:23:29,500 --> 00:23:35,332
and they were about love and
relationships

264
00:23:46,840 --> 00:23:50,399
The news about the western dance
disease spreading in Estonia...

265
00:23:50,400 --> 00:23:52,879
quickly reached Moscow

266
00:23:52,880 --> 00:23:56,474
But this time,
nothing was done about it

267
00:23:56,720 --> 00:24:00,518
Honour to our Leninist Party!

268
00:24:00,600 --> 00:24:03,959
Andropov's cunning plan is launched

269
00:24:03,960 --> 00:24:07,119
It is obvious that Brezhnev
is fading fast

270
00:24:07,120 --> 00:24:09,799
Long live peace!

271
00:24:09,800 --> 00:24:13,439
Behind Brezhnev's back, there's
a fierce struggle for power

272
00:24:13,440 --> 00:24:16,239
Trouble on the ideological front...

273
00:24:16,240 --> 00:24:22,679
is a trump card in the hands
of Andropov's KGB men

274
00:24:22,680 --> 00:24:28,279
The horrified leader of Soviet Estonia
is scared for his own skin

275
00:24:28,280 --> 00:24:30,519
He dashes to Moscow to assure...

276
00:24:30,520 --> 00:24:34,751
that he will take control
of the situation himself

277
00:24:38,280 --> 00:24:40,999
The men in power have a very
clear plan

278
00:24:41,000 --> 00:24:44,239
The disco epidemic must be tamed

279
00:24:44,240 --> 00:24:47,479
The racoon must become a poodle!

280
00:24:47,480 --> 00:24:50,639
We have many neologisms
from the word "disco"

281
00:24:50,640 --> 00:24:52,719
They've already become rooted...

282
00:24:52,720 --> 00:24:55,639
just like a tree planted by a DJ

283
00:24:55,640 --> 00:24:57,239
In every corner of the country...

284
00:24:57,240 --> 00:24:59,719
activists from the Soviet
youth group Komsomol...

285
00:24:59,720 --> 00:25:02,299
are told to master
the enemy's moves

286
00:25:02,300 --> 00:25:06,809
A sexy form, but filled with
Soviet content

287
00:25:13,480 --> 00:25:15,919
So, what are the problems
with disco dancing?

288
00:25:15,920 --> 00:25:18,759
First of all, we are
reinventing the wheel here

289
00:25:18,760 --> 00:25:23,079
Disco is danced all over the world,
but we didn't hear of it...

290
00:25:23,080 --> 00:25:26,355
nor see what the others were doing

291
00:25:30,460 --> 00:25:33,019
Alas, these moves are too late!

292
00:25:33,020 --> 00:25:37,318
The rhythm of the times
is completely different

293
00:25:47,440 --> 00:25:49,879
The Soviet Union attacks Afghanistan

294
00:25:49,880 --> 00:25:54,777
Their relationship with the West
becomes very strained

295
00:25:57,120 --> 00:25:59,999
In order to reinforce the home front...

296
00:26:00,000 --> 00:26:04,551
the puppet rulers of the small
Soviet Republics are replaced

297
00:26:10,600 --> 00:26:14,079
Moscow appoints a new
Party Secretary for Estonia

298
00:26:14,080 --> 00:26:18,239
His name is Karl Vaino.
An old railroad man

299
00:26:18,240 --> 00:26:22,979
He has to direct the local life
back onto the iron rails

300
00:26:22,980 --> 00:26:27,279
And so, here's our generation
marching in front of the cameras

301
00:26:27,280 --> 00:26:30,679
With paper flowers
and Estonian folk costumes

302
00:26:30,680 --> 00:26:35,616
We are waving to Karl Vaino
and he is waving back

303
00:26:38,100 --> 00:26:42,954
Instead of disco, the TV shows
a completely different dance

304
00:26:50,400 --> 00:26:55,037
But somewhere far away,
there is a war raging

305
00:27:01,360 --> 00:27:04,919
Karl Vaino makes his first visit
to Finland

306
00:27:04,920 --> 00:27:09,351
An enormous bronze Lenin
is erected there

307
00:27:14,860 --> 00:27:18,359
Everyone has a sour smile
on their face

308
00:27:18,360 --> 00:27:23,377
Soviet Union is marking
its area of influence

309
00:27:23,420 --> 00:27:26,479
But above that area,
through houses and cities...

310
00:27:26,480 --> 00:27:33,110
over land and sea, the TV waves
float - uncaught!

311
00:27:41,740 --> 00:27:43,139
At the beginning...

312
00:27:43,140 --> 00:27:47,299
not all the villagers understood
what I was talking about

313
00:27:47,300 --> 00:27:49,279
But in about one month...

314
00:27:49,280 --> 00:27:51,759
they started asking questions
in the shop queue, like:

315
00:27:51,760 --> 00:27:56,594
"So, what's new in 'Dallas'?"

316
00:27:59,960 --> 00:28:02,359
When it snowed during winter...

317
00:28:02,360 --> 00:28:05,519
I ran from house to house
with Jaak's letters...

318
00:28:05,520 --> 00:28:07,879
and everywhere, my visit was
long awaited

319
00:28:07,880 --> 00:28:11,239
Everyone wanted to know
what had happened in "Dallas"

320
00:28:11,240 --> 00:28:12,879
And so I told them

321
00:28:12,880 --> 00:28:15,299
Those, who were worthy

322
00:28:15,300 --> 00:28:21,098
J.R. wants to prove to the judges that
Sue Ellen is an alcoholic

323
00:28:30,300 --> 00:28:33,399
The sun is shining
and people are happy

324
00:28:33,400 --> 00:28:38,632
A football game takes place,
followed by a rock concert

325
00:28:43,960 --> 00:28:47,439
And then,
a proper youth riot...

326
00:28:47,440 --> 00:28:50,279
against life in the ridiculous
Soviet Union...

327
00:28:50,280 --> 00:28:54,690
something that Karl Vaino
has come to symbolise

328
00:28:59,600 --> 00:29:02,239
The militia beats the rioters apart

329
00:29:02,240 --> 00:29:04,999
The culprits are looked for
and found

330
00:29:05,000 --> 00:29:09,039
Naturally, it is all the
punk rockers' fault

331
00:29:20,100 --> 00:29:23,319
But how do the young people
in Soviet Estonia know...

332
00:29:23,320 --> 00:29:28,535
how to be a punk rocker?
They've seen it on Finnish TV!

333
00:29:32,820 --> 00:29:36,399
And whose fault is it that young
people watch Finnish...

334
00:29:36,400 --> 00:29:39,079
rather than Soviet Estonian TV?

335
00:29:39,080 --> 00:29:43,059
Naturally, the management
of Estonian Television

336
00:29:43,060 --> 00:29:44,839
Here they are

337
00:29:44,840 --> 00:29:50,497
They are ordered to come up
with measures against Finnish TV

338
00:29:50,520 --> 00:29:52,959
The Programme Director,
Voldemar Lindstrom...

339
00:29:52,960 --> 00:29:55,399
is called to Party headquarters...

340
00:29:55,400 --> 00:29:59,179
and for starters, he gets
a harsh talking-to

341
00:29:59,380 --> 00:30:05,639
Finnish TV was naturally
a headache for Party leaders

342
00:30:05,640 --> 00:30:15,852
Estonian media was blamed for not fighting
against it with necessary means...

343
00:30:15,853 --> 00:30:19,679
and for not spreading
different information

344
00:30:19,760 --> 00:30:22,879
Now, "the necessary means"'
have to be found

345
00:30:22,880 --> 00:30:25,519
The Party officials' plan
is this:

346
00:30:25,520 --> 00:30:28,559
Estonian TV is watched
both here and in Finland...

347
00:30:28,560 --> 00:30:31,439
so our channel should make
everyone believe...

348
00:30:31,440 --> 00:30:35,159
how wonderful the life
in Soviet Estonia really is

349
00:30:35,160 --> 00:30:39,191
It should take centre stage
in its full glory

350
00:30:43,740 --> 00:30:49,739
The school uniform consists
of a skirt and a jacket...

351
00:30:49,740 --> 00:30:53,119
And indeed, Estonian shows do
become popular in Finland...

352
00:30:53,120 --> 00:30:55,499
but in an unexpected way

353
00:30:55,500 --> 00:30:59,776
It becomes source material for
several Finnish humour shows

354
00:31:01,377 --> 00:31:14,400
(mocking jabber imitating a Soviet
official speaking Estonian)

355
00:31:15,100 --> 00:31:18,619
Karl Vaino decides that such
mockery must end

356
00:31:18,620 --> 00:31:22,619
A full-scale campaign against
Finnish TV begins

357
00:31:22,620 --> 00:31:25,799
Vaino fires the first shots
of this war in Moscow...

358
00:31:25,800 --> 00:31:28,799
at the Congress of the
Communist Party:

359
00:31:28,800 --> 00:31:32,079
Due to its geographical situation...

360
00:31:32,080 --> 00:31:36,239
Estonia is in the front line
of the ideological battle

361
00:31:36,240 --> 00:31:45,219
In a place, where the fire of
anti-Soviet propaganda is fierce

362
00:31:45,220 --> 00:31:50,259
Lately, the acts of the
ideological enemy...

363
00:31:50,260 --> 00:31:54,839
have turned especially cruel and
mean!

364
00:31:54,840 --> 00:31:58,515
It's psychological warfare!

365
00:32:06,840 --> 00:32:13,114
Spring. The last episode of the
season. J.R. is alone in his office

366
00:32:14,740 --> 00:32:16,459
Someone enters

367
00:32:16,460 --> 00:32:20,959
Two shots!
J.R. falls down

368
00:32:20,960 --> 00:32:24,916
End credits.
Who shot J.R.?

369
00:32:26,320 --> 00:32:28,639
I posted a letter to Urve...

370
00:32:28,640 --> 00:32:32,079
and promised to continue writing
in the autumn

371
00:32:32,280 --> 00:32:37,334
Then I went to Young Pioneer camp,
like every summer

372
00:32:37,460 --> 00:32:43,909
I got Jaak's last letter.
He wrote that J.R. has been shot

373
00:32:45,660 --> 00:32:53,019
He grabbed his heart and fell.
There was blood...

374
00:32:53,220 --> 00:32:55,239
But I couldn't tell the villagers
that...

375
00:32:55,240 --> 00:32:58,079
nothing's going to happen
before the autumn

376
00:32:58,080 --> 00:33:00,659
Everyone was so eager to
hear about it

377
00:33:00,660 --> 00:33:07,217
And so I made up my own version
of what happened

378
00:33:09,900 --> 00:33:12,179
Specialists confirm that...

379
00:33:12,180 --> 00:33:18,412
the primary targets were the minds
of Soviet Estonian children

380
00:33:38,040 --> 00:33:42,299
There are very interesting
CIA documents...

381
00:33:42,300 --> 00:33:44,599
about the work to be done
with the youth

382
00:33:44,600 --> 00:33:48,099
One very important thing
they considered was that...

383
00:33:48,100 --> 00:33:54,415
that in 1985, a new generation
will enter the stage

384
00:33:56,220 --> 00:34:01,952
Here, our generation runs to the stage
with flowers for Karl Vaino

385
00:34:01,980 --> 00:34:04,139
We have no idea that...

386
00:34:04,140 --> 00:34:09,139
a cunning plan is being hatched
at Party headquarters

387
00:34:09,140 --> 00:34:12,299
The secret order signed by Vaino
mentions...

388
00:34:12,300 --> 00:34:16,099
"the measures for neutralising the
influence of bourgeois television..."

389
00:34:16,100 --> 00:34:18,859
"on the inhabitants of the Republic"

390
00:34:18,860 --> 00:34:23,359
In this document, they shoot at
Finnish TV without aiming

391
00:34:23,360 --> 00:34:27,179
The city and district committees
of the Communist Party...

392
00:34:27,180 --> 00:34:31,179
as well as the other
central offices...

393
00:34:31,180 --> 00:34:36,179
should make it their main task
to battle the...

394
00:34:36,180 --> 00:34:42,879
politically hostile influence of
bourgeois TV

395
00:34:42,880 --> 00:34:47,539
Strict orders and prohibitions
pour onto us from Vaino's offices...

396
00:34:47,540 --> 00:34:50,735
like ice cold rain

397
00:34:56,480 --> 00:34:58,339
When I was in the third grade...

398
00:34:58,340 --> 00:35:01,219
my grandfather was taken to
the hospital with a floating kidney

399
00:35:01,220 --> 00:35:04,131
My business went downhill

400
00:35:04,620 --> 00:35:07,819
My grandfather was treated
at Karl Marx hospital, where...

401
00:35:07,820 --> 00:35:11,339
the Finnish converters
were removed from TV sets

402
00:35:11,340 --> 00:35:17,355
The same was probably done
in all state facilities

403
00:35:23,200 --> 00:35:27,039
Grandfather said that's why
his kidney stopped floating...

404
00:35:27,040 --> 00:35:32,173
it got so boring at the hospital
he just had to get back home

405
00:35:32,220 --> 00:35:37,659
The countermeasures became
quite strange

406
00:35:37,660 --> 00:35:41,139
For example, the Party's
attempts to remove...

407
00:35:41,140 --> 00:35:50,351
antennas directed at Finland
from Tallinn's rooftops

408
00:35:51,460 --> 00:35:53,979
This seemingly ordinary man,
Nikolai...

409
00:35:53,980 --> 00:35:57,739
is one of the first victims
of the evil campaign

410
00:35:57,740 --> 00:36:01,259
One fine morning, there are
some comrades with a saw...

411
00:36:01,260 --> 00:36:03,379
on the roof of his home

412
00:36:03,380 --> 00:36:07,979
They left one antenna standing
and took away the rest

413
00:36:07,980 --> 00:36:12,353
They had been ordered to
"just take them all down"

414
00:36:21,360 --> 00:36:23,659
We didn't have much to watch here

415
00:36:23,660 --> 00:36:28,339
The Estonian films or
war movies from Russian TV

416
00:36:28,340 --> 00:36:30,339
How long can you watch those?

417
00:36:30,340 --> 00:36:33,179
I wanted to see what was
happening abroad

418
00:36:33,180 --> 00:36:38,216
Finnish TV brought the
rest of the world to us

419
00:36:38,220 --> 00:36:41,539
Important men, somewhere high up,
had no idea that...

420
00:36:41,540 --> 00:36:46,099
they have acquired a
rather dangerous enemy

421
00:36:46,100 --> 00:36:49,139
Nikolai happens to be
a passionate inventor

422
00:36:49,140 --> 00:36:51,859
Soon, a counter-plan is born
in a kitchen

423
00:36:51,860 --> 00:36:54,896
But we will get there...

424
00:36:55,300 --> 00:36:59,099
Long meetings are held
and reports written...

425
00:36:59,100 --> 00:37:01,939
about the battle
against Finnish TV

426
00:37:01,940 --> 00:37:07,338
Especially in the regions where
Finnish TV can't be seen

427
00:37:07,420 --> 00:37:10,579
Where it can be seen,
the meetings are shorter...

428
00:37:10,580 --> 00:37:13,779
in order to make it to home
to watch Finnish TV

429
00:37:13,780 --> 00:37:21,457
Brezhnev's Soviet Union has already
split into parallel realities

430
00:37:27,780 --> 00:37:32,619
The devastating news about
the great loss to our country...

431
00:37:32,620 --> 00:37:40,379
and to the Communist Party
hit the collective farmers very hard

432
00:37:40,380 --> 00:37:46,619
For us, agricultural workers,
it was a particularly painful loss

433
00:37:46,620 --> 00:37:51,659
Let us not forget that
it was Leonid Brezhnev...

434
00:37:51,660 --> 00:37:54,579
under whose leadership
and direction...

435
00:37:54,580 --> 00:38:01,732
the objectives for the agricultural
industry were devised...

436
00:38:01,820 --> 00:38:05,800
It is 12:45 and...

437
00:38:05,900 --> 00:38:09,499
...the coffin was lowered
into the grave

438
00:38:18,500 --> 00:38:20,779
After the demise of Brezhnev...

439
00:38:20,780 --> 00:38:25,695
the way to power is
finally open for Andropov

440
00:38:26,080 --> 00:38:38,999
Dear comrades! Let me thank you
from the bottom of my heart...

441
00:38:39,000 --> 00:38:43,019
The Soviet Union rediscovers
an old truth...

442
00:38:43,020 --> 00:38:49,372
things aren't advancing because
people are stupid and lazy

443
00:39:00,000 --> 00:39:05,590
An era of fervent campaigning begins

444
00:39:17,280 --> 00:39:20,359
As a result of one of these
campaigns...

445
00:39:20,360 --> 00:39:24,239
a People's Militia is compiled
of ordinary people

446
00:39:24,240 --> 00:39:28,979
They patrol the streets at night
for aimless wanderers, drunks...

447
00:39:28,980 --> 00:39:32,719
or thieves of public property

448
00:39:32,720 --> 00:39:35,559
Dear members of the People's Militia

449
00:39:35,560 --> 00:39:42,675
The patrol's mission for
today is this: we've planned...

450
00:39:42,676 --> 00:39:47,319
Nikolai and thousands of
others have started...

451
00:39:47,320 --> 00:39:52,639
building TV antennas
from junkyard scraps

452
00:39:53,920 --> 00:39:56,799
I built my first antenna
for my own TV

453
00:39:56,800 --> 00:40:02,539
Just find an iron pipe, I already
had a welding machine

454
00:40:02,540 --> 00:40:07,399
I did have to steal
some pieces of pipe

455
00:40:07,400 --> 00:40:11,755
That's how it all started

456
00:40:11,756 --> 00:40:15,239
First, you needed a copper pipe

457
00:40:15,240 --> 00:40:19,279
It was an interesting time,
an era of 'do it yourself'

458
00:40:19,280 --> 00:40:23,439
First, I made one for myself.
Then, one for a friend

459
00:40:23,440 --> 00:40:28,752
Then for a friend of a friend,
and so it went on

460
00:40:28,800 --> 00:40:31,279
There were plenty of orders

461
00:40:31,280 --> 00:40:35,292
After a while, I was mass producing
antennas

462
00:40:50,400 --> 00:40:58,111
This is me, Toomas. Here's
me at home and here, at school

463
00:40:58,160 --> 00:41:02,179
Those are the two places,
where I spend most of my time

464
00:41:02,200 --> 00:41:05,959
After school, the children
whose parents worked late...

465
00:41:05,960 --> 00:41:10,159
were taken to the grass field
by the school...

466
00:41:10,160 --> 00:41:12,559
and told to form football teams

467
00:41:12,560 --> 00:41:15,990
Usually, I was a reserve player

468
00:41:18,720 --> 00:41:21,519
My mother was part of
the People's Militia

469
00:41:21,520 --> 00:41:24,599
They were entitled to buy things
from the factory cafeteria...

470
00:41:24,600 --> 00:41:26,959
that were not available in stores:

471
00:41:26,960 --> 00:41:31,159
canned peas, frankfurters
and tangerines

472
00:41:31,160 --> 00:41:34,079
In the evenings,
mother patrolled on the streets...

473
00:41:34,080 --> 00:41:37,519
I was allowed to watch TV
until quarter to ten...

474
00:41:37,520 --> 00:41:41,632
then I had to wash my teeth
and go to sleep

475
00:41:41,680 --> 00:41:44,439
Sometimes, I watched a bit longer

476
00:41:44,440 --> 00:41:51,152
I couldn't fall sleep anyway
before my mother came back

477
00:41:53,840 --> 00:41:55,959
Across the gulf, in Helsinki...

478
00:41:55,960 --> 00:42:00,039
electronics shops are being
bought out of one item:

479
00:42:00,040 --> 00:42:02,679
microcircuits

480
00:42:02,680 --> 00:42:05,719
What are people using
them for?

481
00:42:05,720 --> 00:42:07,999
The time of colour television
has come...

482
00:42:08,000 --> 00:42:12,359
and some enterprising Finns have
discovered a prosperous business

