The chips, hidden in clothes or body cavities,
are smuggled to Estonia

484
00:42:16,760 --> 00:42:21,279
Here, they are sold to scalpers
for a substantial profit

485
00:42:21,280 --> 00:42:26,319
And they resell them to engineers
who use them for colour decoders

486
00:42:26,320 --> 00:42:31,359
The chip was small, you could
fit 50 in one cigarette box...

487
00:42:31,360 --> 00:42:34,919
and the currency rate between
Finnish marks and roubles...

488
00:42:34,920 --> 00:42:38,659
was better with microchips
than with jeans

489
00:42:38,660 --> 00:42:41,919
The Soviet customs officials
have to toughen up...

490
00:42:41,920 --> 00:42:46,239
and start catching
the chip smugglers

491
00:42:46,240 --> 00:42:51,199
"What are our Finnish guests up to?"
asks this propaganda film

492
00:42:51,200 --> 00:42:55,039
Tallinn is the fourth most popular
destination in the USSR...

493
00:42:55,040 --> 00:42:57,999
for tourists from capitalist
countries

494
00:42:58,000 --> 00:42:59,999
Not all of them come here...

495
00:43:00,000 --> 00:43:02,759
for their sincere interest
towards our way of life

496
00:43:02,760 --> 00:43:05,199
A propagandist should never
forget this...

497
00:43:05,200 --> 00:43:10,159
as he comes into contact with
foreigners every day

498
00:43:10,160 --> 00:43:19,399
There is vileness, amorality and
an empty soul behind...

499
00:43:19,400 --> 00:43:28,557
their superficial kindness.
That's the face of capitalism

500
00:43:28,558 --> 00:43:32,658
Calling all law enforcement
officers!

501
00:43:33,260 --> 00:43:37,939
Underground microchip sales
are prospering

502
00:43:37,940 --> 00:43:43,576
An intensive campaign begins
to catch the speculators

503
00:43:44,277 --> 00:43:46,677
- Hello
- Hello

504
00:43:53,840 --> 00:43:59,799
One autumn evening in the early 1980's,
my father took me for a ride

505
00:43:59,800 --> 00:44:04,759
He didn't say a word. We drove
somewhere in Mustamae district

506
00:44:04,760 --> 00:44:08,479
I remember him constantly
glancing in the mirror

507
00:44:08,480 --> 00:44:11,979
He parked the car away
from the entrance

508
00:44:11,980 --> 00:44:15,859
I was to go in, take the elevator
to the 4th floor and...

509
00:44:15,860 --> 00:44:19,720
ring the bell at
door number 45

510
00:44:19,800 --> 00:44:25,479
That was how my father got
the chips to build new blocks

511
00:44:25,480 --> 00:44:28,799
The man in a bathrobe
was a dealer

512
00:44:28,800 --> 00:44:31,559
It was a strictly forbidden job

513
00:44:31,560 --> 00:44:35,838
But that evening was
very important for me

514
00:44:35,839 --> 00:44:41,350
Now, I was part of the same
secret society as my father

515
00:44:42,560 --> 00:44:47,359
I wasn't allowed to talk about it
at school. And I didn't!

516
00:44:47,360 --> 00:44:51,759
Hands on the table! Mouths shut!
Backs straight!

517
00:44:51,760 --> 00:44:53,671
And what are you doing?

518
00:44:54,680 --> 00:45:02,099
I took the no 7 trolley and
the no 26 bus home from school

519
00:45:02,100 --> 00:45:07,671
But the other commuters
didn't know my true identity

520
00:45:07,672 --> 00:45:13,539
In the autumn of 1984, Finnish TV
started showing "Knight Rider"

521
00:45:17,940 --> 00:45:23,379
Just a few months later, it had
become an integral part of my life

522
00:45:23,380 --> 00:45:26,071
It was about a car

523
00:45:27,520 --> 00:45:32,919
With the push of a button, it
could jump over other cars

524
00:45:32,920 --> 00:45:36,759
Michael Knight taught me to use
my watch to talk to cars

525
00:45:36,760 --> 00:45:38,679
And I did talk...

526
00:45:38,680 --> 00:45:43,859
to all 14 foreign cars I knew of
in Tallinn in those days

527
00:45:43,860 --> 00:45:46,879
Dear members of the People's Militia

528
00:45:46,880 --> 00:45:51,559
Three groups are heading
to residential areas

529
00:45:51,560 --> 00:46:01,259
Pay attention to cars and underage
persons gathering around them

530
00:46:01,260 --> 00:46:04,399
There was a foreign car
in our yard too

531
00:46:04,400 --> 00:46:07,375
A sailor had bought a Renault

532
00:46:07,376 --> 00:46:12,119
It was the only car
that mattered

533
00:46:12,120 --> 00:46:16,479
But one day, I saw a boy
from building no 37...

534
00:46:16,480 --> 00:46:20,639
using his watch to talk
to MY car

535
00:46:20,640 --> 00:46:24,076
I think I was quite upset

536
00:46:25,540 --> 00:46:28,659
But soon enough,
everyone was doing it

537
00:46:28,660 --> 00:46:32,474
All you needed was a digital watch

538
00:46:44,740 --> 00:46:48,439
On February 9th, 1984, the Secretary
General of the Communist Party...

539
00:46:48,440 --> 00:46:52,559
Yuri Vladimirovich Andropov,
passed away

540
00:46:58,020 --> 00:47:03,159
The fervent campaigns end
just as suddenly as they started

541
00:47:03,160 --> 00:47:06,754
Life goes back to normal

542
00:47:14,500 --> 00:47:19,317
But the Americans are preparing
the final blow

543
00:47:22,340 --> 00:47:29,453
First, as if by coincidence,
Finnish TV shows "Star Wars"

544
00:47:29,960 --> 00:47:35,348
Of course, we, Estonian children,
are completely blown away

545
00:47:35,349 --> 00:47:39,750
Flying saucers appear in
our asphalt drawings

546
00:47:39,751 --> 00:47:42,959
This rare shot of a school play
shows...

547
00:47:42,960 --> 00:47:47,379
the Soviet Estonian version of
Jedi Knights

548
00:47:47,380 --> 00:47:52,999
There are hundreds of satellites
beeping above us in space

549
00:47:53,000 --> 00:47:58,037
The superpowers have
their own star wars

550
00:48:02,960 --> 00:48:07,220
Americans have challenged
the Russians

551
00:48:07,221 --> 00:48:13,519
They launch satellites to destroy
the Soviet nuclear missiles

552
00:48:13,520 --> 00:48:15,819
In return, the Russians want
to build missiles...

553
00:48:15,820 --> 00:48:18,759
that penetrate the American
protective shield

554
00:48:18,760 --> 00:48:21,779
But these missiles
are very expensive

555
00:48:21,780 --> 00:48:27,632
The project had no connection
to reality. It was a daydream

556
00:48:27,633 --> 00:48:34,639
The Soviet Union took the bait and
never caught up with America

557
00:48:35,760 --> 00:48:39,719
I saw on TV that Michael Knight
visited Finland

558
00:48:39,720 --> 00:48:43,188
It was the closest meeting we ever had

559
00:48:48,160 --> 00:48:53,014
Estonians knew that soon,
there would be an atomic war

560
00:48:58,980 --> 00:49:02,859
In the school hall, they showed
us films about atomic bombs...

561
00:49:02,860 --> 00:49:05,499
and carried out bomb threat drills

562
00:49:05,500 --> 00:49:07,879
Should an atomic bomb
fall on Tallinn...

563
00:49:07,880 --> 00:49:13,359
we are to put on gas masks and
go to the school cloakroom

564
00:49:13,360 --> 00:49:15,739
It doubled as our bomb shelter

565
00:49:15,740 --> 00:49:18,599
Soon enough, a few of us
discover that...

566
00:49:18,600 --> 00:49:22,299
if you push the filter of a
gas mask to your mouth...

567
00:49:22,300 --> 00:49:28,519
you can make the sound of
Michael Knight's car, KITT

568
00:49:28,520 --> 00:49:33,896
From then on, atomic war
seemed pretty cool to us

569
00:49:34,520 --> 00:49:41,219
At the same time, the Soviet economy's
only focus is the military production

570
00:49:41,220 --> 00:49:47,519
It is wise to hit the shops early
if you expect to get any goods

571
00:49:47,520 --> 00:49:50,457
There's never enough of anything

572
00:50:01,200 --> 00:50:08,819
Only canned squid and baranki
(dry bagels) are left

573
00:50:08,820 --> 00:50:15,819
That's when we meet Vaiski -
the face of Finnish food ads

574
00:50:15,820 --> 00:50:20,919
Meat counter ready for inspection
- Well, this is not an inspection

575
00:50:20,920 --> 00:50:23,799
We're just looking at it
through the client's eyes

576
00:50:23,800 --> 00:50:27,839
Oh, what a beautiful veal,
pork and lamb!

577
00:50:27,840 --> 00:50:31,119
Vaiski and the army of
cutlets and steaks...

578
00:50:31,120 --> 00:50:34,079
arrive on the front lines of the
Cold War during the hottest battle

579
00:50:34,080 --> 00:50:36,999
For Estonians standing
in long queues...

580
00:50:37,000 --> 00:50:40,799
Vaiski becomes nothing less
than a fairy tale hero

581
00:50:40,800 --> 00:50:47,719
The message of the ad is an
effective propaganda weapon

582
00:50:47,720 --> 00:50:50,079
"What good things will Vaiski
think up next?"

583
00:50:50,080 --> 00:50:54,019
"A delicious roast. From a
particularly good fillet..."

584
00:50:54,020 --> 00:50:55,479
The Estonian officials announce that...

585
00:50:55,480 --> 00:50:59,239
the delicacies in the ads
are just plastic fakes and...

586
00:50:59,240 --> 00:51:03,079
the Finns couldn't
afford them anyway

587
00:51:03,080 --> 00:51:05,219
"The delightful sauce will
make your mouth water..."

588
00:51:05,220 --> 00:51:11,233
And Mr Vaiski must be on the payroll
of the American secret service!

589
00:51:13,860 --> 00:51:17,639
General Dreyfus of American
military intelligence has said:

590
00:51:17,640 --> 00:51:20,519
"In the ideological battle
with Communists..."

591
00:51:20,520 --> 00:51:25,157
"we do not need the truth,
we need subversion."

592
00:51:25,780 --> 00:51:30,839
In addition to our good influence,
the influence of the Party...

593
00:51:30,840 --> 00:51:33,599
there is another,
hostile influence...

594
00:51:33,600 --> 00:51:37,479
continuously affecting
the Soviet people

595
00:51:37,480 --> 00:51:41,759
We all know that they are
trying very hard to do this

596
00:51:41,760 --> 00:51:48,799
The Finns were harshly criticised
for their "Americanness"

597
00:51:48,800 --> 00:51:55,632
And we didn't know it was because
the Soviets felt genuinely threatened

598
00:51:56,133 --> 00:51:57,799
LUNCH BREAK

599
00:51:57,800 --> 00:52:02,079
The village talked of nothing
but "Dallas"

600
00:52:02,080 --> 00:52:07,111
Even the band of the
collective farm sang about "Dallas"

601
00:52:07,840 --> 00:52:10,919
But in the autumn,
the people of our village...

602
00:52:10,920 --> 00:52:13,559
sent a joint letter to
Estonian Television and...

603
00:52:13,560 --> 00:52:16,679
Party Central Committee,
stating that they have...

604
00:52:16,680 --> 00:52:19,399
a collective farm with
record-breaking results...

605
00:52:19,400 --> 00:52:21,879
a winner of the
Socialist Competition...

606
00:52:21,880 --> 00:52:24,759
and wouldn't it be possible
to show "Dallas"...

607
00:52:24,760 --> 00:52:27,719
on an Estonian
or Leningrad channel

608
00:52:27,720 --> 00:52:30,959
It all led to very big trouble

609
00:52:30,960 --> 00:52:34,919
A commission from the District
Committee came to investigate

610
00:52:34,920 --> 00:52:39,119
People were questioned,
a meeting held, fingers pointed...

611
00:52:39,120 --> 00:52:41,239
and it was explained to the people...

612
00:52:41,240 --> 00:52:44,759
that this was not proper
entertainment for Soviet people

613
00:52:44,760 --> 00:52:46,919
The head of the village board and...

614
00:52:46,920 --> 00:52:51,137
the Pioneer leader
of the school were replaced

615
00:52:53,640 --> 00:52:57,839
So we heard nothing more
about Dallas

616
00:52:57,840 --> 00:53:02,639
I still waited for Jaak's letters,
but he had taken up football...

617
00:53:02,640 --> 00:53:06,219
and didn't have time
to write anymore

618
00:53:06,220 --> 00:53:10,275
I still have some of his old letters

619
00:53:12,020 --> 00:53:16,239
An anonymous engineer writes
a letter to a newspaper

620
00:53:16,240 --> 00:53:20,559
He recommends building
a gigantic metallic net...

621
00:53:20,560 --> 00:53:23,319
in the gulf between
Estonia and Finland...

622
00:53:23,320 --> 00:53:27,414
that would catch
the Finnish TV waves

623
00:53:33,820 --> 00:53:36,999
Vaino likes the idea very much

624
00:53:37,000 --> 00:53:41,949
The management of Estonian TV is
called to Party headquarters

625
00:53:42,020 --> 00:53:46,379
As always, the meeting starts
with a harsh talking-to

626
00:53:46,380 --> 00:53:50,139
They were very stern
and direct

627
00:53:50,140 --> 00:53:54,279
We thought that they will shoot us
on the spot

628
00:53:54,280 --> 00:53:59,839
Vaino was clear that
a system has to be built...

629
00:53:59,840 --> 00:54:08,015
to prevent hostile channels
from spreading in Estonia

630
00:54:09,400 --> 00:54:12,079
The TV management tries
to convince Vaino that...

631
00:54:12,080 --> 00:54:19,900
such a net would be complicated,
expensive and still useless

632
00:54:25,440 --> 00:54:32,439
Engineers suggested building the
net on an island in the Gulf...

633
00:54:32,440 --> 00:54:41,020
to make it hundreds of meters tall,
so it could block the Finnish TV signal

634
00:54:42,760 --> 00:54:45,799
An overall anxiety spreads

635
00:54:45,800 --> 00:54:49,319
Among others,
Nikolai prepares for resistance

636
00:54:49,320 --> 00:54:52,159
It is time to build a simple
but efficient invention:

637
00:54:52,160 --> 00:54:55,539
A mercury antenna!

638
00:54:55,540 --> 00:55:01,799
You had to cut off the tip
of a thermometer...

639
00:55:01,800 --> 00:55:10,519
insert a hairline thread into the
tube of mercury

640
00:55:10,520 --> 00:55:21,680
You push it into the mercury
and pull back a bit

641
00:55:21,681 --> 00:55:25,959
Then you connect the thread
to your TV set

642
00:55:25,960 --> 00:55:33,159
It receives the signal much better
than an ordinary antenna

643
00:55:34,660 --> 00:55:40,559
But it jams the reception of other
receivers in a 3-5 km radius

644
00:55:40,576 --> 00:55:48,259
Next to us, there was a missile
base with two nuclear warheads

645
00:55:48,260 --> 00:55:51,899
It was inspected and
guarded very well

646
00:55:51,900 --> 00:55:56,159
As soon as the antenna
starts to jam the waves...

647
00:55:56,160 --> 00:56:03,253
they will try to locate
the source. And they'll find it

648
00:56:03,920 --> 00:56:08,837
Then you had to quickly
unplug the antenna

649
00:56:09,140 --> 00:56:12,159
The thermometer fever
spreads fast

650
00:56:12,160 --> 00:56:16,869
The pharmacies of Tallinn are
emptied of their thermometer stocks

651
00:56:16,870 --> 00:56:19,039
65 kopecks a piece

652
00:56:19,040 --> 00:56:23,939
The authorities claim it is
due to a flu outburst...

653
00:56:23,940 --> 00:56:29,859
but in fact, it was
a different kind of epidemic

654
00:56:29,860 --> 00:56:32,919
Even more, the virus from Estonia...

655
00:56:32,920 --> 00:56:38,357
spreads quickly
all over the Soviet Union

656
00:56:38,400 --> 00:56:43,359
In many cities, videotapes with
Finnish subtitles are discovered

657
00:56:43,360 --> 00:56:46,879
The narrator with the nasal voice
becomes famous

658
00:56:46,880 --> 00:56:48,879
He sits in a basement
somewhere in Leningrad...

659
00:56:48,880 --> 00:56:52,735
and dubs these films
into Russian

660
00:57:10,480 --> 00:57:14,999
Hollywood movies reach
Estonia via Finnish TV

661
00:57:15,000 --> 00:57:18,559
and from Estonia they spread
all over the Soviet Union...

662
00:57:18,560 --> 00:57:22,658
from Lithuania to Turkmenistan

663
00:57:29,600 --> 00:57:33,519
It would have been easy
to arrest The Nasal Man

664
00:57:33,520 --> 00:57:38,672
But he remained free, so we know
that wasn't the authorities' plan

665
00:57:38,760 --> 00:57:44,379
True enough, the real plan was
far bigger

666
00:57:44,380 --> 00:57:47,839
Later studies claim that
for decades...

667
00:57:47,840 --> 00:57:55,019
Soviet Estonia had been a
secret laboratory of the KGB

668
00:57:55,020 --> 00:57:59,439
They researched what will
happen to a Soviet citizen...

669
00:57:59,440 --> 00:58:04,154
when flooded with
hostile propaganda

670
00:58:07,140 --> 00:58:13,139
In some areas, detailed
experiments were carried out

671
00:58:13,140 --> 00:58:19,856
How else could they research
the impact of this sort of thing?

672
00:58:19,857 --> 00:58:22,959
This explains the regular
TV audience surveys...

673
00:58:22,960 --> 00:58:25,839
that were forbidden elsewhere
in the Soviet Union

674
00:58:25,840 --> 00:58:29,719
These surveys can be compared to
obtaining intelligence data from...

675
00:58:29,720 --> 00:58:36,330
a social environment in order
to create new weapons

676
00:58:37,440 --> 00:58:41,119
Karl Vaino, who knew nothing
about the secret laboratory...

677
00:58:41,120 --> 00:58:43,519
has been led to complain, to weep...

678
00:58:43,520 --> 00:58:48,519
and conduct powerless campaigns
against Finnish TV

679
00:58:48,520 --> 00:58:54,199
Soviet authorities did possess the
technology to block Finnish TV signals

680
00:58:54,200 --> 00:58:58,199
Radio-technologically, the Soviet Union
was a very powerful country

681
00:58:58,200 --> 00:59:02,879
The jamming transmitters would have
been produced in military plants...

682
00:59:02,880 --> 00:59:09,413
and installed without any involvement
from Estonian technicians

683
00:59:10,660 --> 00:59:17,839
We, Estonian children, have been
the KGB's lab rats for years

684
00:59:17,840 --> 00:59:22,439
They've been preparing us
with the help of Finnish TV

685
00:59:22,440 --> 00:59:27,479
We are meant to be the new
generation of Soviet spies...

686
00:59:27,480 --> 00:59:32,439
raised amidst the influence of
western popular culture

687
00:59:32,440 --> 00:59:38,958
But the deadly virus has
broken out of the lab

688
00:59:38,959 --> 00:59:42,479
By the mid-1980s,
the KGB realises that...

689
00:59:42,480 --> 00:59:49,013
the "soft power" of pop culture
is overpowering the regime

690
00:59:56,640 --> 01:00:01,519
Furthermore, the empire is
falling apart at the seams

691
01:00:01,520 --> 01:00:05,879
The price of oil dropped below
prime cost. Soviet Union earns less

692
01:00:05,880 --> 01:00:13,035
The Space Race ate resources.
The result was an economic collapse

693
01:00:34,580 --> 01:00:40,131
The memory of Konstantin
Chemenko will last forever

694
01:00:44,040 --> 01:00:46,199
On the verge of collapsing,
the USSR starts...

695
01:00:46,200 --> 01:00:49,959
to warm relations
with the Americans

696
01:00:49,960 --> 01:00:52,879
The new leader of the
bankrupt country, Gorbachev...

697
01:00:52,880 --> 01:00:56,399
must save the little
that's left to save

698
01:00:56,400 --> 01:01:00,999
Meanwhile, the ever deluded
Karl Vaino relies on an old trick:

699
01:01:01,000 --> 01:01:05,319
when the end is near,
act like everything is fine

700
01:01:05,320 --> 01:01:09,959
We, the veterans of the
army and the Party...

701
01:01:09,960 --> 01:01:15,192
are convinced that you,
our young friends...

702
01:01:15,193 --> 01:01:22,430
will carry on the flag of peace,
good will and Communism

703
01:01:26,920 --> 01:01:29,879
Instead of folk costumes,
the lab rats are now...

704
01:01:29,880 --> 01:01:34,199
wearing parachute satchels
and we're marching

705
01:01:34,200 --> 01:01:39,234
But there is an air of spring
and decay around us

706
01:01:45,240 --> 01:01:47,879
That spring I decided...

707
01:01:47,880 --> 01:01:51,639
I will not wear blue socks
and brown sandals

708
01:01:51,640 --> 01:01:53,039
I will not!

709
01:01:53,040 --> 01:01:57,459
The teacher sent me home
because of my sneakers

710
01:01:57,460 --> 01:01:59,599
But I don't care

711
01:01:59,600 --> 01:02:04,039
It's May. School's almost
out and summer will begin

712
01:02:04,040 --> 01:02:08,239
But not just any summer,
THE summer

713
01:02:08,240 --> 01:02:12,478
In 52 days, Finnish TV
will show "Emmanuelle"

714
01:02:12,479 --> 01:02:17,499
It is a famous erotic movie

715
01:02:17,500 --> 01:02:19,419
Fresh out of the hospital...

716
01:02:19,420 --> 01:02:23,639
my grandfather sent
a cake box to his friends

717
01:02:23,640 --> 01:02:25,479
Guess what was inside?

718
01:02:25,480 --> 01:02:29,574
Yes, a Finnish TV block
made by my father

719
01:02:31,780 --> 01:02:36,119
Meanwhile, Gorbachev is
on a world tour, like a pop star

720
01:02:36,120 --> 01:02:39,319
His perestroika movement
has to demolish...

721
01:02:39,320 --> 01:02:44,711
the harsh image of the Soviet Union

722
01:02:47,460 --> 01:02:52,559
In Finland, Misha is welcomed
like an old friend

723
01:02:52,560 --> 01:02:55,271
The nightmare is fading

724
01:02:55,272 --> 01:03:01,279
A lot of time has passed since the last
Soviet leader visited Finland

725
01:03:01,280 --> 01:03:05,239
There's a feeling of change
in the air

726
01:03:05,240 --> 01:03:07,319
Then, Gorbachev
flies to Tallinn

727
01:03:07,320 --> 01:03:10,379
The meeting begins with
a harsh talking-to

728
01:03:10,380 --> 01:03:18,599
My friend Karl Vaino tells me that
everything is fine in Estonia

729
01:03:18,600 --> 01:03:24,319
But I know better. The leaders
have lost touch with the people

730
01:03:24,320 --> 01:03:29,719
They are cooped up in their offices
and that leads to mistakes

731
01:03:29,720 --> 01:03:33,059
They want to control everything

732
01:03:33,060 --> 01:03:37,419
Even the customary kisses
now seem cold

733
01:03:37,420 --> 01:03:40,199
Maybe this is when Gorbachev
whispers to Vaino...

734
01:03:40,200 --> 01:03:45,518
that the expensive net in
the Gulf is a definite no-go

735
01:03:45,519 --> 01:03:52,029
The visit is carried out
with bitter smiles

736
01:04:07,060 --> 01:04:14,378
This is me, Jaak. It's summer and I'm
at Young Pioneer camp again

737
01:04:16,660 --> 01:04:20,699
In the mornings, they woke
us with a blaring fanfare

738
01:04:20,700 --> 01:04:23,839
You had to dress very quickly

739
01:04:23,840 --> 01:04:27,399
Nobody knew why we
had to hurry...

740
01:04:27,400 --> 01:04:31,799
because afterwards we
just lazed around

741
01:04:31,800 --> 01:04:36,259
But even in my sleepy haze,
I knew: it's June 24

742
01:04:36,260 --> 01:04:38,499
The day has arrived!

743
01:04:38,500 --> 01:04:43,151
That evening, Finnish TV
will show "Emmanuelle"

744
01:04:44,020 --> 01:04:46,893
Our relatives in
Southern Estonia...

745
01:04:46,894 --> 01:04:50,719
start driving to Tallinn
early in the morning

746
01:04:50,720 --> 01:04:56,271
By lunchtime, only children and
old ladies were left in the South

747
01:04:56,272 --> 01:05:02,219
The rest headed to Tallinn
in their cars

748
01:05:02,220 --> 01:05:06,659
Because in Tallinn you see
Finnish TV

749
01:05:06,660 --> 01:05:10,919
By 4:15 PM, there are
112 cars parked...

750
01:05:10,920 --> 01:05:14,299
on the football ground
next to our school

751
01:05:14,300 --> 01:05:18,839
The sum of the licence plate
numbers is even for 63 cars...

752
01:05:18,840 --> 01:05:25,590
and odd for 49 cars. There are
no foreign cars, only Russian

753
01:05:25,591 --> 01:05:28,671
The Polish Fiat doesn't count

754
01:05:28,672 --> 01:05:31,399
Mother says that there must be...

755
01:05:31,400 --> 01:05:35,312
a big party or song festival
somewhere

756
01:05:36,700 --> 01:05:41,319
Today, we are making
nest boxes for starlings

757
01:05:41,320 --> 01:05:44,499
The sides have to be sawed
into neat pieces...

758
01:05:44,500 --> 01:05:47,859
and a hole drilled into
the front board

759
01:05:47,860 --> 01:05:50,919
We are supervised by
our teacher

760
01:05:50,920 --> 01:05:55,869
But when we look at each
other, we start giggling...

761
01:05:56,720 --> 01:05:59,619
Dear members of the People's Militia

762
01:05:59,620 --> 01:06:05,710
The patrol's mission for
today is this...

763
01:06:06,580 --> 01:06:09,919
In the evening,
the streets are empty

764
01:06:09,920 --> 01:06:15,450
Just a few pigeons... and
my mom patrolling somewhere

765
01:06:15,451 --> 01:06:18,851
KVASS (bread drink)

766
01:06:21,160 --> 01:06:27,119
"But everyone is watching it," I say.
"Not everyone," says my mom

767
01:06:27,120 --> 01:06:30,219
"For instance, you will not
watch it"

768
01:06:30,220 --> 01:06:34,657
I got even by not brushing
my teeth that night

769
01:06:41,400 --> 01:06:45,799
At 10 o'clock, everyone goes to
brush their teeth

770
01:06:45,800 --> 01:06:48,679
Half past 10,
it's bed call

771
01:06:48,680 --> 01:06:54,159
Usually, we tell jokes
and giggle. But not today

772
01:06:54,160 --> 01:06:56,919
On the other side of the wall,
in the teacher's lounge...

773
01:06:56,920 --> 01:07:01,688
a TV is on.
Everyone is waiting

774
01:07:55,960 --> 01:08:00,532
Suddenly, I realised
how this world works

775
01:08:00,533 --> 01:08:05,759
There are those who only get
a few coins for a TV guide...

776
01:08:05,760 --> 01:08:09,979
and then those who get the
crisp banknotes

777
01:08:09,980 --> 01:08:13,479
Those who fetch the cake box
from the dealer...

778
01:08:13,480 --> 01:08:19,659
and then those who sell its
content for 400 roubles

779
01:08:19,660 --> 01:08:25,597
And I didn't want to be
the loser any more

780
01:08:49,300 --> 01:08:53,519
The TV signal was so weak that...

781
01:08:53,520 --> 01:08:56,659
I decided to try out the
mercury antenna

782
01:08:56,660 --> 01:09:00,997
It worked for me, but messed
up the neighbours' TV

783
01:09:00,998 --> 01:09:05,939
As soon as I plugged it in,
they lost reception

784
01:09:05,940 --> 01:09:11,039
I could watch for 30 min before a
jeep from the missile base arrived

785
01:09:11,040 --> 01:09:15,239
So I unplugged the antenna

786
01:09:19,800 --> 01:09:22,819
When the jeep left, I
plugged the antenna back in

787
01:09:22,820 --> 01:09:27,511
Of course I kept watching

788
01:09:39,740 --> 01:09:44,959
They said that if we
jam their radars...

789
01:09:44,960 --> 01:09:48,399
they may accidentally
launch something...

790
01:09:48,400 --> 01:09:54,052
and when that baby is out,
who knows what will happen

791
01:10:02,540 --> 01:10:06,159
The atomic war doesn't
break out just then

792
01:10:06,160 --> 01:10:11,893
Luckily enough, the erotic movie
ends before that

793
01:10:21,060 --> 01:10:25,553
For some reason, I woke up
at 12:42 PM

794
01:10:25,554 --> 01:10:27,954
It was light outside

795
01:10:27,955 --> 01:10:34,232
I thought that war had broken out
and my mom's on the frontlines

796
01:10:34,233 --> 01:10:38,519
But then I saw it - hundreds
of cigarettes glowing...

797
01:10:38,520 --> 01:10:46,052
like fireflies on every balcony
of the opposing houses

798
01:10:52,560 --> 01:10:58,899
A kind of bomb had been dropped
on Estonia and it ended the Cold War

799
01:10:58,900 --> 01:11:05,156
The bliss of freedom soon
spreads all over the country

800
01:11:18,860 --> 01:11:24,109
The Soviet Union surrenders
quickly and entirely

801
01:11:24,110 --> 01:11:29,473
Only the men in fur hats
wave from the sinking ship

802
01:11:29,474 --> 01:11:33,119
But not all of them go
down with the sinking ship

803
01:11:33,120 --> 01:11:37,918
Some of them have
their life boats ready

804
01:12:05,600 --> 01:12:11,695
There are theories about the
KGB destroying the system...

805
01:12:11,696 --> 01:12:15,299
just to be able to rebuild it again

806
01:12:15,300 --> 01:12:24,999
Today's actions were actually
planned way back then

807
01:12:27,200 --> 01:12:32,420
Loyal Vaino is not one of
the chosen few

808
01:12:32,421 --> 01:12:38,400
He gives up his post
in the summer of 1988

809
01:12:38,401 --> 01:12:42,639
He immediately heads to Moscow
where he's still happily retired

810
01:12:42,640 --> 01:12:48,139
He has never visited Estonia
during these 20 years and...

811
01:12:48,140 --> 01:12:51,119
has given only one interview,
to a German TV journalist

812
01:12:51,120 --> 01:12:55,079
"When did you realise that Estonia
would become independent...

813
01:12:55,080 --> 01:12:58,479
and this process couldn't
be overturned?"

814
01:12:58,480 --> 01:13:05,599
I believe that it's connected to
Finnish TV

815
01:13:05,600 --> 01:13:10,079
People saw that life was
more free elsewhere...

816
01:13:10,080 --> 01:13:14,277
that others had more
opportunities...

817
01:13:14,278 --> 01:13:19,479
their standard of life
was higher than in Estonia

818
01:13:19,480 --> 01:13:21,490
They asked, "How can that be?"

819
01:13:21,491 --> 01:13:27,380
"How can they have all that
in a rotting capitalism?"

820
01:13:27,940 --> 01:13:35,035
That got people thinking

821
01:13:35,850 --> 01:13:48,159
Despite being forbidden, there
were antennas on every balcony

822
01:13:48,160 --> 01:13:55,025
Banning them made no difference

823
01:14:02,235 --> 01:14:08,300
Long live the workers of
the Soviet Union! Hurray!

824
01:14:08,301 --> 01:14:11,800
And so we marched
to a song festival...

825
01:14:11,801 --> 01:14:14,459
holding paper flowers and
wearing folk costumes

826
01:14:14,460 --> 01:14:19,999
But we weren't waving to Karl
Vaino and he wasn't waving back

827
01:14:20,000 --> 01:14:26,590
We were waving to ourselves,
in a completely different era

828
01:14:58,780 --> 01:15:05,091
Urve, Joosep, Jaak and Toomas are
now leading completely ordinary lives

829
01:15:05,092 --> 01:15:10,020
9 months after Finnish TV showed
"Emmanuelle", the birth rate in Estonia
soared to a high

830
01:15:10,021 --> 01:15:12,930
There have been 37 sequels
to "Emmanuelle"

831
01:15:12,931 --> 01:15:16,900
Nikolai works on a ship travelling
between Estonia and Finland

832
01:15:16,901 --> 01:15:19,950
He has yet to patent his
mercury antenna

833
01:15:19,951 --> 01:15:23,920
J.R. was shot by his mistress,
but he survived

834
01:15:23,921 --> 01:15:28,500
The final episode of "Dallas"
aired in 1991 - the same year
the Soviet Union disappeared

835
01:15:28,501 --> 01:15:33,558
The Cold War resumed after
a short break
